Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author      AutomatedContainerPrep
    Description Base image for QA-symlink exercise – provides Python and pytest and guarantees a writable /home/user.

%post
    set -e

    # Update APT metadata and install Python + pip.
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip

    # Install pytest for the forthcoming test suites.
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Ensure that /home/user exists and is writable by any unprivileged user who
    # will run inside the container.
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Minimise image size.
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Make sure the location where pip installs executables is in the PATH.
    export PATH="/usr/local/bin:${PATH}"

%runscript
    # Default runscript: just execute whatever the caller supplied.
    exec "$@"

%help
    This container supplies a pristine Ubuntu 22.04 userland with Python 3 and
    pytest installed, plus an empty, world-writable /home/user directory required
    by the QA-symlink assignment’s initial-state tests.